The Three Advanced Indicators

These come from market microstructure and volatility clustering, not normal chart patterns.

1️⃣ Volatility Compression → Expansion (VCE)

Before many large runs, volatility drops to unusually low levels.

Pattern:

large move potential =
very quiet price action
+ tightening daily ranges
+ increasing volume

This is often called a volatility squeeze.

Why it matters:

Markets tend to move from low volatility → explosive volatility.

Goblin rule:

if ATR (volatility) is near a 30-day low
AND volume is rising
→ breakout probability increases


⸻

2️⃣ Liquidity Vacuum Indicator

Small caps often explode when there is very little sell liquidity above the current price.

Signs:
	•	stock approaches 52-week high
	•	very few sellers remain
	•	short interest high

Result:

price gap upward

This is what happened with AAOI.

Goblin rule:

price within 5% of yearly high
+ float under ~200M shares


⸻

3️⃣ Options Skew Signal

Sometimes options traders move before stock traders.

Key sign:

call volume spike
+
implied volatility jump

This often happens days before big news.

Goblin rule:

call volume > 3x normal


